title: cmd/*: Illegal Instruction on Mac OS X
body:
by **ben@skylandlabs.com**: 
What steps will reproduce the problem?
If possible, include a link to a program on play.golang.org.
1. Install LuaJIT-2.0.1 and "make && sudo make install" it.
2. "go run" the following program: http://play.golang.org/p/1UUm4pGoTb

What is the expected output?

Hello from Lua!


What do you see instead?

go build command-line-arguments: signal: illegal instruction


Which compiler are you using (5g, 6g, 8g, gccgo)?

6c

Which operating system are you using?

Mac OS X 10.7.5

$ uname -a
Darwin blackdog2.local 11.4.2 Darwin Kernel Version 11.4.2: Thu Aug 23 16:25:48 PDT
2012; root:xnu-1699.32.7~1/RELEASE_X86_64 x86_64


Which version are you using?  (run 'go version')

go version devel +d58997478ec6 Mon Apr 08 00:09:35 2013 -0700 darwin/amd64


Please provide any additional information below.

Here's the full compile. It seems to die on 6c

$ go run -work -x lj.go 
WORK=/var/folders/p3/nqt2bgp17fn7_t9hr6tr_1m00000gn/T/go-build089425085
mkdir -p $WORK/command-line-arguments/_obj/
mkdir -p $WORK/command-line-arguments/_obj/exe/
cd /tmp/go-luajit
/usr/local/go/pkg/tool/darwin_amd64/cgo -objdir $WORK/command-line-arguments/_obj/ -- -I
$WORK/command-line-arguments/_obj/ lj.go
/usr/local/go/pkg/tool/darwin_amd64/6c -F -V -w -I $WORK/command-line-arguments/_obj/ -I
/usr/local/go/pkg/darwin_amd64 -o $WORK/command-line-arguments/_obj/_cgo_defun.6 -D
GOOS_darwin -D GOARCH_amd64 $WORK/command-line-arguments/_obj/_cgo_defun.c
go build command-line-arguments: signal: illegal instruction
